Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX ID™ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: RegistryNumber
Columns.Description: This is the number assigned by the state office.

Columns.Name: IncorporationState
Columns.Description: This may include any of the 50 U.S. states plus Washington, D.C.; only the "domestic" incorporation state is returned.

Columns.Name: BusinessRegisteredName
Columns.Description: The business name provided at the time of registration.

Columns.Name: FilingDate
Columns.Description:
This is the date the state recorded as the paperwork transaction date. It may or may not be the same as the incorporation date. 

This date will usually change annually and is used to indicate when the most recent update was received by the state. It is possible that the fi ling date is
several years old because the state did not update a "lapsed or inactive fi ling".

Columns.Name: IncorporationDate
Columns.Description:
This is the date of the original fi ling of incorporation papers.

It will not change from year to year. 

This is not the date the business fi led the papers with the state.

Columns.Name: EquifaxBusinessRegistrationStatusTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an  Equifax business registration status type.
